1983 JUEGOS PANAMERICANOS (Pan-American Games)

For amateur players.

QUALIFYING

North America:

6/7 East Rutherford, USA  1-1  Canada
  [Giants Stadium]
  [Goals: Dave Lischner 8' / Igor Vrablic 15']
  [USA: Jeff Duback, Dan D'Angelo, Mike Fox, Tom Isirov (Amr Aly), Jim Kavanaugh,
        Dave Lischner, Doug Puffenbarger (Jeff Hooker), Tim Schulz, Bobby Smith,
        John Stollmeyer, Kazbek Tambi.]
  [Canada: Don Ferguson, John Connor, Paul Lee, Jamie Lowery, Craig Martin,
           Ed McNally, Norm Odinga, George Pakos (Robbie Cleugh), Alan Spink, Dan Sudeyko,
           Igor Vrablic.]

10/7 Hamilton, Canada  2-3  USA
  [McMaster Stadium]
  [Goals: Dan Sudeyko, Norm Odinga 87' / Mike Fox 12' 51', Jeff Hooker 62']
  [Ref: Rex Osborne]
  [Canada: Don Ferguson, John Connor (Robbie Cleugh), Ken Garraway (Norm Odinga), Paul Lee,
           Jamie Lowery, Craig Martin, Ed McNally, George Pakos, Alan Spink,
           Dan Sudeyko, Igor Vrablic.]
  [USA: Tim Harris, Amr Aly, Paul Caligiuri, Dale Ervine (Dan D'Angelo), Mike Fox, Jeff Hooker,
        Jim Kavanaugh, Dave Lischner, Kevin Maher, John Stollmeyer, Kazbek Tambi.]

USA qualified 4-3 on aggregate.


Central America and Caribbean:

Presumably Mexico, Cuba, and Bermuda qualified based on their positions in the 1982 Juegos
Centroamericanos y del Caribe. It is not clear how Guatemala qualified.


South America:

Venezuela qualified as hosts.
Brazil, Uruguay, and Argentina qualified as the top three teams in the 
1983 South American Youth Championship.  Bolivia (who were fourth) withdrew
and were replaced by Chile.



FINAL TOURNAMENT - Caracas, Venezuela

The original draw was:
Group A: Chile, Surinam, Venezuela
Group B: Bermuda, Brazil, USA
Group C: Argentina, Guatemala, Honduras
Group D: Cuba, Mexico, Uruguay
However Surinam and Honduras did not arrive, and the draw was changed at the last minute.


